body:
In the line that I marked with "BUG" I get a stacktrace. It exists also on the current nigtly version.

Test out by yourself https://github.com/AlexanderMattheis/filter/tree/217144a8101a99b797448e4b220be6db72751575

From my side it does not make any sense why it shouldn't work. The full code you find in `src/logic/statistics`.

I tried this code:

```rust
fn get_distribution_parameters(histogram: &[u32; NUMBER_OF_HISTOGRAM_BINS], num_pixels: usize) -> HistogramDistribution {
    let mut sum_a = 0;
    let mut sum_b = 0;

    for i in 0..NUMBER_OF_HISTOGRAM_BINS {
        let value = (i as u32) * (histogram[i] as u32);

        sum_a += value;
        sum_b += (i as u32) * value;  // BUG: i * (value as usize) works, but why?
    }

    let a = sum_a as f64;
    let b = sum_b as f64;
    let count_reciprocal = 1.0 / (num_pixels as f64);

    return HistogramDistribution {
        average: count_reciprocal * a,
        variance: (b - count_reciprocal * (a * a)) * count_reciprocal,
    };
}
```

